/* gamedata-w2-fishing.mjs — World-2 (Yum-Yum Desert) Fishing Town: Poppy's fish-town, the Tar
 * Pit, Mega Fish milestones, and the Reset Spiral / shiny-fishing sub-systems.
 * GENERATED by a one-off extraction script (scratchpad, not committed); refresh after a major
 * patch.
 *
 * ============================================================================================
 * WHERE THE DATA LIVES IN N.js
 * ============================================================================================
 * POPPY_UPGRADES and TAR_PIT_UPGRADES are BOTH slices of ONE shared CustomLists table:
 *
 *   na.Owlz = function() { return [ ...29 rows... ] }        N.js:23722
 *   registered as CustomLists.Owlz (e.g. N.js:30249: `e=na.Owlz();b.h.Owlz=e`)
 *
 * Despite the name "Owlz" (an internal/placeholder dev name — the string literally never
 * appears as a UI label anywhere we found), this table is shared by THREE unrelated minigames,
 * back-to-back, no separators other than row order:
 *   rows  0- 8 (9 rows)  — Orion / Feather Generation (World 4-ish "feather fairy", NOT in
 *                          scope for this file — included in the header only so the row-offset
 *                          arithmetic below makes sense).
 *   rows  9-20 (12 rows) — POPPY_UPGRADES (Owlz[9+i], i=0..11).
 *   rows 21-28 (8 rows)  — TAR_PIT_UPGRADES (Owlz[21+i], i=0..7).
 * The "+9" and "+21" base offsets are independently confirmed FOUR separate ways in N.js (not
 * just asserted): (1) RooNextUpgReq reads `Owlz[9+GenINFO[12]][3]`; (2) RooCost reads
 * `Owlz[b+9][1..2]`; (3) RooCost_T reads `Owlz[b+21][1..2]`; (4) the generic tooltip formatter
 * (N.js:20007-20009) reads `Owlz[f+9+12*accountOptions[287]][6]` — accountOptions[287] is a
 * 0/1 "which panel" flag, so 287=0 -> Owlz[f+9] (Poppy), 287=1 -> Owlz[f+9+12]=Owlz[f+21]
 * (Tar Pit). All four land on the same +9/+21 split. RAW ROW SHAPE (space-split, verbatim):
 *   [0]=name ("Two|Line" piped display name, kept verbatim), [1]=x1, [2]=x2, [3]=x3
 *   (fish-currency unlock threshold; literal "Nah" for every Tar Pit row — Tar Pit upgrades are
 *   gated by slot-count, not a fish threshold, see RooTarOwned below), [4]=bonus label template,
 *   [5]=description template, [6]=x6 (scaling constant used by the template placeholders).
 * Numbers with a literal ".0" suffix in the source (e.g. "150000.0") are kept as plain numbers
 * here — Number()/parseFloat() coercion is exact for all of them (no rounding lost).
 *
 * CROSS-CHECK vs idleon-toolbox (data/website-data.json `poppyBonuses`/`poppyTarBonuses`, and
 * parsers/world-2/kangaroo.ts which mis-names this whole system "kangaroo" — it is Poppy/the
 * Fishing Town, no relation to the actual Kangaroo/Kihmichi-Puffshroom content): 20/20 rows
 * (12 Poppy + 8 Tar Pit) match EXACTLY on name/x1/x2/x3/bonus/desc/x6, 0 mismatches. Every
 * field in every row was independently re-derived from na.Owlz() above, not copied from
 * toolbox's JSON — toolbox was used only as the cross-check target.
 *
 * TEMPLATE PLACEHOLDER LEGEND (bonus/desc strings) — independently confirmed in N.js at the
 * generic tooltip formatter, N.js:20007-20009 (reads `accountOptions[DN4]` where
 * `DN4 = 268 + 29*accountOptions[287] + i`, i.e. 268+i for Poppy, 297+i for Tar Pit — the SAME
 * level-storage bases as below):
 *   '{'  -> commaNotation(level * x6)
 *   ']'  -> round(100 + level*x6) / 100                          (an "]x" flat multiplier)
 *   '~'  -> notateNumber(100*(1 - 1/(1 + level*x6/100)), "Small") (a "cheaper by ~%" curve)
 *   '?'  -> notateNumber(x6 * (level/(40+level)), "Small")        (saturating "+?%" curve)
 * matches idleon-toolbox's kangaroo.ts `formatDescription` verbatim — that function is CONFIRMED
 * against the live client here, not just taken on trust.
 *
 * MEGA_FISH_MILESTONES descriptions and RESET_SPIRAL descriptions are NOT CustomLists rows —
 * they are literal `this._GenINFO.push("...|...|...")` string pushes inside the constructor of
 * the Poppy/Tar-Pit NPC's behaviour script, `scripts.ActorEvents_670` (class registered at
 * N.js:19604; `PixelHelperActor[25]` is the live instance, cast via
 * `n.__cast(a.engine.getGameAttribute("PixelHelperActor")[25].behaviors.getBehavior(
 * "ActorEvents_670"), Ga)` throughout the dispatcher — this single class ALSO drives Orion,
 * a "Bravery" sword minigame, a harp minigame, and several other unrelated systems bundled into
 * the same `_GenINFO` instance array; only the fields relevant to fishing are used here):
 *   megaFishDesc (12, pipe-joined)   N.js:20890 — byte-for-byte identical to toolbox's
 *                                    `megaFishDesc` array in kangaroo.ts.
 *   resetBonusesDesc (5, pipe-joined) N.js:20891 — byte-for-byte identical to toolbox's
 *                                    `resetBonusesDesc` array.
 *
 * ============================================================================================
 * accountOptions (== save key OptLacc / OptionsListAccount) INDEX MAP
 * ============================================================================================
 * All indices below were independently re-derived from the `_customBlock_Summoning` dispatcher
 * (N.js:18071-18162, the "Roo*" case arms — "Roo" is the internal short-name for this whole
 * system, unrelated to the actual in-game Kangaroo NPC) and the buy/reset click-handler
 * (N.js:19966-20018, the `_TRIGGEREDtext.indexOf("b")` branch). Every index in this list has a
 * DIRECT read or write site cited; none are transcribed from toolbox without independent
 * confirmation, EXCEPT where flagged "not independently located" below.
 *   [267]            fish currency, spent on Poppy upgrades. RooCost/RooNextUpgReq both read it
 *                     directly; the reset routine sets it to 5 (not 0 — a starting stipend).
 *   [268..278]       levels of POPPY_UPGRADES[0..10] (Owlz[9+i]); `accountOptions[268+b]` is
 *                     read in RooCost's pow() term and written (+1, rounded) in the buy handler.
 *                     [268] (upgrade 0, "Tasty Fishbait") ALSO feeds `1+accountOptions[268]` as
 *                     RooCost's `DNSM.RooDN1` base-multiplier seed when b===0, AND as a
 *                     `10*accountOptions[268]` additive term inside RooCatchFishQTY (fish/min).
 *   [279]            POPPY_UPGRADES[11] ("Greatest Catch") level = cumulative Mega Fish tier
 *                     count. RooMegafeather(b) = `accountOptions[279]>b ? (b===11 ?
 *                     accountOptions[279]-11 : 1) : 0` (N.js:18083-18084) — confirmed by formula
 *                     match only; the exact statement that INCREMENTS [279] on a "Greatest
 *                     Catch" purchase was not located within the time budget (see Formulas /
 *                     honesty note below) — flagged, not independently confirmed for the write
 *                     side, only the read side.
 *   [269]..[278]     (individual upgrade levels, see [268..278] above) — [269]="Quick Reeling"
 *                     (catch-req reducer, RooCatchREQ), [270]="Shiny Lure" (shiny base rate,
 *                     RooCatchRate_S), [271] is NOT an upgrade level — see below, [272]="fishy
 *                     discount" (cost reducer, RooCost), [273]="Juicy Worm" (RooCatchFishQTY
 *                     term), [275]="Fisheroo Reset" (gates both baseFishRate's extra term AND
 *                     RooCatchRate_S's), [276]="Lightning Quickness" (shiny-req reducer,
 *                     RooCatchREQ_S), [277]="Fisheroo Investing" (feeds the reset-point-grant
 *                     formula below), [278]="Multihook Fishing" (RooCatchFishQTY term).
 *   [271]            a SEPARATE "player Fishing-Buddy level" driving the flat `bonusData` block
 *                     (Fishing Eff/Defence/Fishing XP/Accuracy/Total DMG/AFK Gains/Cash) via
 *                     RooBonuses (N.js:18084-18086+): `base[k] * baseMultiplier *
 *                     max(0,ceil((accountOptions[271]-offset[k])/7))`, offsets 0..6, bases
 *                     3/3/5/2/2/0.5/3 — matches Mega Fish milestone 5's flavor text ("The
 *                     Fishing Buddy upgrade now gives +50% Bluefin caught... per Lv past Lv.5").
 *                     `baseMultiplier = (1+LegendPTS_bonus(26)/100) * (1+Companions(51)) *
 *                     (1+RooBonusAll/100)`, RooBonusAll = the totalFishRate sum below.
 *   [280]            a SECOND fish-caught counter, incremented in perfect lockstep with [267]
 *                     everywhere both are touched (N.js:19699, N.js:19966) and zeroed together
 *                     with [267]'s sibling fields on a Fisheroo Reset. Used ONLY for a UI
 *                     tutorial gate ("Click the pond..." shows while accountOptions[280]<100,
 *                     N.js:19994) — NOT read by RooNextUpgReq (which compares [267] directly
 *                     against Owlz[9+i][3]). Toolbox's kangaroo.ts uses [280] as "progress" for
 *                     the `unlocked` flag; since [267] and [280] move together except possibly
 *                     mid-tick, this is behaviorally equivalent but NOT the field the live
 *                     unlock-check actually reads — flagged as a minor toolbox inaccuracy, not
 *                     ours.
 *   [281..286]       6 SHINY_MULTI_TIERS levels (RooShinyMulti reads
 *                     `accountOptions[round(281+b)]`, b=0..5).
 *   [287]            0/1 UI panel toggle (0=viewing Poppy, 1=viewing Tar Pit) — reused
 *                     arithmetically as the `+12` term in the generic tooltip formatter's row
 *                     offset (see above). Not a save-worthy "progress" value, just current-tab
 *                     state, but it DOES persist in the save like everything else in this array.
 *   [288]/[289]      running Bluefin-catch-progress / shiny-catch-progress accumulators
 *                     (ticked by RooCatchRate/RooCatchRate_S each timer pulse, N.js:19966-19968,
 *                     19699); [289] is also the numerator toolbox calls `shinyProgress`.
 *   [290]            UNSPENT Reset Spiral points, granted on a Fisheroo/Greatest-Catch reset:
 *                     `accountOptions[290] += 10 + 5*RooMegafeather(2) +
 *                     accountOptions[302]("Tarrific Resets" tar-upgrade level) +
 *                     accountOptions[277]("Fisheroo Investing" level)` (N.js:19970-19971).
 *                     The "+5*RooMegafeather(2)" term is EXACTLY Mega Fish milestone 2's flavor
 *                     text ("gives +5 Pts when Fisheroo Resetting"). NOT documented in
 *                     idleon-toolbox's parser at all — found independently while tracing the
 *                     reset click-handler.
 *   [291..295]       5 RESET_SPIRAL invested-point levels (RooRESETbon reads
 *                     `accountOptions[291+b]`, b=0..4) — see RESET_SPIRAL table below. These
 *                     are NOT reset by the small "Fisheroo Reset"; only zeroed inside the
 *                     Greatest-Catch branch (guarded by a check whose trigger condition we could
 *                     NOT confirm — see honesty note).
 *   [296]            tar-fish currency owned, spent on TAR_PIT_UPGRADES via RooCost_T
 *                     (N.js:20614 buy handler: `accountOptions[296] >= RooCost_T(i)`).
 *   [297..304]       levels of TAR_PIT_UPGRADES[0..7] (Owlz[21+i]); `accountOptions[297+b]` read
 *                     in RooCost_T's pow() term (and, oddly, ADDED to the multiplicative cost —
 *                     confirmed verbatim in N.js, not a transcription slip, see Formulas below).
 *                     [300]="Fishy Reductions" (feeds RooCost's cost-reduction axis 2),
 *                     [301]="Super Tarbait" (feeds RooCatchREQ_T), [302]="Tarrific Resets" (feeds
 *                     the [290] point-grant formula), [304]="King Worm" (feeds RooCost's/
 *                     RooCost_T's third cost-reduction axis, gated by RooMegafeather(10) i.e.
 *                     Mega Fish milestone 10 — matches that milestone's flavor text "All
 *                     upgrades... are 5% cheaper per LV of King Worm upgrade").
 *   [305]            tar-fish catch-progress accumulator (RooCatchRate_T ticks it, mirrors
 *                     [288]/[289]'s pattern for the third resource).
 *   [274]            gates the Reset Spiral UI panel (`accountOptions[274]>=1` to view it,
 *                     N.js:19690/19995) and is zeroed inside the same unconfirmed Greatest-Catch
 *                     branch as [291-295]. No increment site located — flagged, matches
 *                     toolbox's "total Fisheroo Reset count" role by elimination but the write
 *                     side is UNCONFIRMED.
 * HONESTY NOTE on the "Greatest Catch" mega-reset gate: the click-handler computes
 * `this._DN1 = RooBonuses(-1)` right before checking `11===this._DN1` to decide whether to also
 * zero [274]/[290]/[291..295] (N.js:20604-20607) — but RooBonuses(b) with b===-1 unconditionally
 * `return`s 0 (N.js:18086: `-1==b?0:...`), so by direct reading this specific branch looks
 * unreachable through this code path. Either there is a second confirmation/popup flow that
 * performs the actual Mega Fish increment + spiral wipe (most likely, given idle-game UX
 * patterns — a "confirm reset" dialog would set `_TRIGGEREDtext` to a different letter we did
 * not trace), or this is genuinely dead/vestigial code. NOT resolved within this pass — flagged
 * rather than guessed at.
 */

